entries.title: Ukraine preparing for major escalation by Russia, top security official tells Sky News
entries.description: Ukraine is preparing for a major escalation by Russia - possibly even in the next two to three weeks, the Ukrainian president's top security official has said.

entries.title: US congressman who was caught lying steps down from committees
entries.description: A US congressman who lied about his past has stepped down from key committees on Capitol Hill.

entries.title: Blinken says US opposes anything that puts two-state solution 'further from reach' after violence in Jerusalem
entries.description: The United States will "continue to oppose anything" that puts a two-state solution "further from reach" after one of the bloodiest months in the West Bank and East Jerusalem in several years, the US secretary of state has said.

entries.title: Alec Baldwin charged with involuntary manslaughter over fatal shooting on Rust film set
entries.description: Hollywood actor Alec Baldwin has been formally charged in New Mexico with involuntary manslaughter over the fatal shooting of a cinematographer on the set of the western film Rust.

entries.title: Andrew Tate: A timeline from Twitter rows to a Romanian cell
entries.description: Andrew Tate went from being a small-time celebrity - Big Brother contestant, kickboxer, influencer - to a household name for his misogynistic videos, social media bans and high-profile arrest in Romania.

entries.title: 'We don't kidnap, we don't rape, we are fathers': Haiti gang steps in to fill gap left by political failure
entries.description: Arriving in Haiti's capital, Port-au-Prince, the sheer scale of the poverty takes your breath away.

entries.title: Farmworker accused of shooting dead seven colleagues 'was angry over $100 repair bill'
entries.description: A farmworker charged with killing seven people at two mushroom farms in California told police he carried out the shootings after his supervisor demanded he paid $100 (£81) to repair a damaged forklift truck.

entries.title: Woman accused of murdering her lookalike in attempt to fake her own death
entries.description: A woman has been accused of seeking out a lookalike of herself on social media and murdering her in a bid to fake her own death.

entries.title: 'Extra safeguards' coming after AI generator used to make celebrity voices read offensive messages
entries.description: A voice technology company which uses artificial intelligence (AI) to generate realistic speech says it will introduce extra safeguards after its free tool was used to generate celebrity voices reading highly inappropriate statements.

entries.title: Michael Jackson's nephew to play pop star in new biopic after 'worldwide search'
entries.description: Producers of a new biopic about Michael Jackson have cast his nephew to play the late pop singer following a "worldwide search".

entries.title: Biden rules out giving F-16 fighter jets to Ukraine
entries.description: President Biden has said the US will not give Ukraine any F-16 fighter jets.
